history.content: As this is related to grad matters and this is an undergraduate page, I'm not sure we'll be able to help you. Michael Sun is the Adviser for the program (out sick today)

I'm applying for the 5th year masters in EECS and I have a couple questions:
(1) Since I was a transfer student to UCBerkeley, does my Cumulative Undergraduate GPA include my grades before transferring into UCBerkeley (even though that is not accounted for on my UCBerkeley transcript GPA)?
(2) Does the Advanced GPA include my final UCBerkeley GPA since I transferred in as a Junior? Therefore it's the same as the Cumulative Undergraduate GPA?
(3) Does the GPA in the major field of study include classes I took at Community college?
(4) Does the GPA in the major field of study include under and upper div?
history.subject: Graduate Admissions GPA Calculations as a Transfer
